Addition of the angles corresponds to multiplication of the elements of SO(2, R), and taking the opposite angle corresponds to inversion. Thus both multiplication and inversion are differentiable maps.


The affine group in one dimension is another subgroup, consisting of upper triangular matrices with unit lower diagonal entry. It is a two-parameter nonabelian Lie group, so with merely two generators, A, B, s.t. 



