Close Bio


Deepak founded Global Inventures in 1993, following senior roles with European, Japanese, and US based telecommunications companies. Inventures helps technology companies collaborate to build commercially relevant ecosystems and alliances around new technologies and standards. Inventures has created and launched more than 60 such initiatives since its inception and is now part of SmithBucklin Corporation. 
Deepak helped create The Thread Group with the founders during 2013. In addition to his role there and at Inventures, he serves as a Mentor to startups selected by the Miller Center for Social Entrepreneurship at Santa Clara University in Silicon Valley. He holds an honors degree in Physical Chemistry from University College London and a M.Sc in Management and a DIC from Imperial College London. 












