Director
Cam Williams
Lead Architect of IoT Connectivity, Schneider Electric 
Close Bio



Cam works with a global corporate team in Schneider Electric that participates in low power wireless control standard organizations, evaluates current wireless technology, and develops reusable software, interfaces, training & tools for project teams in the company.


Previously Cam worked in the commercial buildings business for Andover Controls and then Schneider Electric, where he developed wireless building solutions and standardized BACnet over zigbee.


Cam is also on the zigbee alliance board of directors where he the chair of the Strategy Committee, Testing & Certification Committee and Foundation Working Group, which oversees the zigbee application layer.


Cam was chair of the zigbee alliance Green Power Task Group to promote and develop an ultra-low power energy harvesting protocol. Cam was also the strategic evangelist, champion, and chair of the working group that merged separate zigbee profiles into one zigbee offering.









