Director
Arnulf Rupp
Senior Director of Business Development and Standardization, Digital Systems Business Unit, OSRAM
Close Bio



Arnulf Rupp was born in Munich, Germany, in 1970. He received a diploma degree in physics from the Technical University of Munich, Germany, in 1997 and a master's degree in business administration from the University of Augsburg, Germany, in 2006.


He has worked for the company OSRAM since 1997 and is currently Senior Director of Business Development and Standardization for the Business Unit Digital Systems. Prior to this position Arnulf Rupp worked as a Senior Director of product development for LED Light Engines. His work experience includes R&D management, strategy consultancy, strategic marketing, automotive product development and power electronics.


As part of his work assignment Arnulf Rupp represents OSRAM in the board of directors and workgroups of multiple organizations including the Thread Group, the Digital Illumination Interface Alliance and the Module Driver Interface Special Interest Group.

















 


































